HEADWORD: Sinapoleic
<hw>Sin`a*po*le"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Sina</ets>pis + <ets>oleic</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Of or pertaining to mustard oil; specifically, designating an acid
of the oleic acid series said to occur in mustard oil.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

